                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="13834290" author="apurtell" created="Wed, 27 Nov 2013 23:02:06 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;No patch, but this is important.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13852306" author="apurtell" created="Wed, 18 Dec 2013 23:29:46 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;No patch, moving out.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14126628" author="enis" created="Tue, 9 Sep 2014 05:25:49 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Linking &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-10602&quot; title=&quot;Cleanup HTable public interface&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-10602&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-10602&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, but this may not be needed anymore with the shiny Table / Admin APIs. Let me check in 0.99.1. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14189807" author="talat" created="Thu, 30 Oct 2014 08:39:57 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=busbey&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;busbey&quot;&gt;Sean Busbey&lt;/a&gt; If you are not working on this, Could I assigning myself... &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14190045" author="busbey" created="Thu, 30 Oct 2014 13:23:25 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;All yours!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14190940" author="stack" created="Thu, 30 Oct 2014 22:19:17 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;We used to specify tables names with byte array or String. In 0.96 we changed it to a TableName class because we added namespaces.&lt;br/&gt;
I think the worry here is that in a few places we let through &apos;ns:tablename&apos; &amp;#8211; a String or byte array with the delimiter in it &amp;#8211; which was a workaround getting namespaces in but we&apos;d like to purge that now.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14190950" author="talat" created="Thu, 30 Oct 2014 22:24:35 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=stack&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;stack&quot;&gt;stack&lt;/a&gt; for introduction about the issue. You know what I need. &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/smile.gif&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt; &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14226679" author="stack" created="Wed, 26 Nov 2014 19:21:44 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Resolving as not a problem.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I took a quick pass over client and mapred* packages.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The regex references to tables as Strings are a bit dodgy but fine for now I&apos;d say. In HConnection there are still a few methods that take a tablename as String but they are deprecated and point at the TableName alternatives.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;d say we&apos;re good enough here.  Lets open explicit issues for API in violation rather than have this nebulous issue as critical.  Reopen if you feel otherwise about it.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14331711" author="enis" created="Sat, 21 Feb 2015 23:46:03 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Closing this issue after 0.99.2 release.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
